When being asked to reword something, do it in a conversational manner, use commas instead of dashes, no semi colons

Always use British English spelling instead of American English spelling. Examples:
- Use "colour" instead of "color"
- Use "normalise" instead of "normalize"
- Use "optimise" instead of "optimize"
- Use "recognise" instead of "recognize"
- Use "organise" instead of "organize"
- Use "centre" instead of "center"
- Use "metre" instead of "meter" (for measurement)
- Use "theatre" instead of "theater"
- Use "analyse" instead of "analyze"
- Use "realise" instead of "realize"
- Use "memorise" instead of "memorize"
- Use "visualise" instead of "visualize"
- Use "finalise" instead of "finalize"
- Use "specialise" instead of "specialize"
- Use "prioritise" instead of "prioritize"
- Use "summarise" instead of "summarize"
- Use "optimisation" instead of "optimization"
- Use "organisation" instead of "organization"
- Use "behaviour" instead of "behavior"
- Use "favour" instead of "favor"
- Use "honour" instead of "honor"
- Use "labour" instead of "labor"
- Use "neighbour" instead of "neighbor"
- Use "defence" instead of "defense"
- Use "licence" (noun) instead of "license" (noun), but "license" (verb) remains the same
- Use "practice" (noun) and "practise" (verb) instead of "practice" for both
- Use "programme" instead of "program" (for schedules/plans), but "program" is fine for computer programs
- Use "travelling" instead of "traveling"
- Use "cancelled" instead of "canceled"
- Use "labelled" instead of "labeled"
- Use "modelling" instead of "modeling"
- Use "cancelling" instead of "canceling"
- Use "labelling" instead of "labeling"